song_name: Save The Life Of My Child

version_description: This is mostly based on the excellent Alan Robinson video which is a transcription of the Paul Simon arrangement. Paul Simon was given it by the great Martin Carthy. The A7sus4add6 looks like a Am7 played on the 3rd fret, and for the Em9no5D just add a 3rd finger to the A7sus4add6 to make a C shape chord (1st finger stays on the 3rd fret). For the CM9 in the intro form a regular Em and touch the C note on the A string momentarily . I arpeggio ad lib all the way through this song but you can strum too.
Showing the timing of the voices for this little known version.
Pluck strings on acoustic using chords listed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-Jj4s9I-53g.
Different key, easier to play for beginner's.
Complete chords for all parts of the song / original tuning: half-step down / short tabs for special parts / suggestions for voicings.
Complete chords for the live version / short tabs for special parts / suggestions for playable voicings / https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q9jgnwwDsDs.
The Strumming pattern for this is, play the base note with thumb and use pluck or strike the following strings.
Chords as heard on the Old Friends Simon and Garfunkel compilation.
